# .gitignore for an Unreal Engine 5.6/5.7 C++ project.
#
# THE RULE: everything UBT or the editor regenerates is ignored; everything that
# IS the project — the .uproject, Source/, Config/, and Content/ — is committed.
# Content/ holds BINARY .uasset/.umap files: they ARE your art/levels/blueprints
# and MUST be committed (Git LFS recommended for large binaries). The dirs below
# are pure build/cache output (per the UE Directory Structure docs) and rebuild
# on the next Generate-Project-Files / build / editor open.

# --- Regenerated / derived (NEVER commit) ---
Binaries/
DerivedDataCache/
Intermediate/
Saved/

# Build/ holds project build scaffolding. The top-level project Build/ is
# generated; ignore it but keep platform receipts a team explicitly checks in by
# un-ignoring as needed. Plugin Binaries/Intermediate are covered by the globs below.
Build/

# Generated IDE project files (UE treats these as pure intermediates — see
# "Project Files for IDEs"; they are never checked in to source control).
*.sln
*.suo
*.xcodeproj/
*.xcworkspace/
.vs/
.vsconfig
.idea/
*.VC.db
*.VC.opendb
*.opensdf
*.sdf
*.user

# Per-plugin generated dirs (a project can have Plugins/<X>/{Binaries,Intermediate}).
Plugins/**/Binaries/
Plugins/**/Intermediate/

# OS cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Committed (do NOT add these to .gitignore) ---
# *.uproject
# Source/
# Config/
# Content/          <-- binary .uasset/.umap; commit them (Git LFS for big files)
# Plugins/<X>/      <-- the plugin's Source/, Config/, Content/, .uplugin
